\f1\i The Problem with \'93Learning Styles\'94 
\f0\i0 by Cindi May, I do like how she is cautious to promote learning styles as an easy fix or a replacement for having productive study strategies. While all students are unique, May reminds us that there are learning methods that have proven to be universally beneficial such as spacing out study sessions, self-testing on material, experiencing the material in multiple formats, and elaborating on material to form connections that we can remember. My feeling is that there is benefit in both the individual learner adopting the methods that they feel are most helpful to them, and using study habits that might require more discipline }